    A Set implementation based on a modified Red-Black Tree. Elements are sorted from least to greatest according to their natural ordering, or by an explicit Comparator provided at creation. Attempting to remove or insert null elements is prohibited. Querying for null elements is allowed. Inserting non-comparable elements will result in a ClassCastException.

    The iterators obtained from the iterator() method are fail-fast. Attempts to modify the elements in this list at any time after an iterator is created, in any way except through the iterator's own remove method, will result in a ConcurrentModificationException.

    This set is not thread-safe. If multiple threads modify this set concurrently it must be synchronized externally.

    This implementation uses a comparator (whether or not one is explicitly provided) to perform all element comparisons. Two elements which are deemed equal by the comparator's compare(E, E) method are, from the standpoint of this set, equal.
